{{Quote|Show due respect. You speak of the only flight of Dinner Squadron, the one X-wing squadron with an undefeated record and no losses.|[[Hohass Ekwesh|Hohass "Runt" Ekwesh]]|<ref name="X-Wing: Solo Command">''[[X-Wing: Solo Command]]''</ref>}}
'''Dinner Squadron''' never truly existed in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] duty rosters; the name was first dreamed up by [[Garik Loran|Garik "the Face" Loran]] during the competition to give "Gray Squadron" (later [[Wraith Squadron]]) a name. He was apparently faint with hunger at the time, according to fellow pilot [[Tyria Sarkin Tainer|Tyria Sarkin]]. [[Kell Tainer]] borrowed the name to describe a tactic used at the [[Battle of Folor]] to distract the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Implacable (Star Destroyer)/Legends|''Implacable'']] from reaching Folor Base and thus discovering the transport [[Borleias (transport)|''Borleias'']], which was unable to take off until it had made engine repairs.

===The fake ''Millennium Falcon'' ploy===
{{Quote|Sensors, does this 'ship of unknown type' match the parameters of the ''Millennium Falcon''?''"<br />"''Sir, they don't match anything. Some sort of odd-shaped thing with an oscillating shield system we can't get a good fix on.|Admiral Apwar Trigit and his sensor officer|<ref name="X-Wing: Wraith Squadron">''[[X-Wing: Wraith Squadron]]''</ref>}}
Kell and [[Hohass Ekwesh|Runt]] boosted the power to their [[Transponder code/Legends|transponder systems]] and [[Deflector shield/Legends|shields]] to make it seem on [[Sensor/Legends|sensors]] as though they had more than just two [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wings]] on site. [[Blue Squadron (New Republic)|Blue Squadron]]'s Blue Nine ([[Dorset Konnair]]) and Blue Ten ([[Tetengo Noor]]), while flying [[RZ-1 A-wing interceptor/Legends|RZ-1 A-wing interceptors]], stayed very close together and oscillated the power to their own shields, giving them a unique sensor signature that was difficult to get a sensor lock on and thus no definitive classification as to what their ship was supposed to be.

The four pilots then used an old encryption code, which was known to have been recently cracked by former [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit]]'s forces to send simulated comm chatter back and forth. Since this was effectively the same as broadcasting in the clear and the pilots were doing their best at pretending to be more notable persons (Kell posed as [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]] while Konnair played [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]]), thus making Trigit believe that they were, in fact, [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] and the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]. The two pilots sent transmissions back and forth that indicated that the "''Falcon''" was unable to reach escape velocity. The Admiral took the bait and moved to intercept the "''Falcon''", allowing the ''Borleias'' to repair and lift off.

Once Trigit realized he had been fooled, he ordered a [[Turbolaser/Legends|turbolaser]] bombardment of the area the four starfighters were hiding in, however impressive piloting on the part of Runt's "student mind" was able to see them all to safety. Dinner Squadron was later used by [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] as the inspiration for the ''[[Millennium Falsehood]]'' and the missions flown therein.

